1:Splitting the String into Words
2.Checking for Words:Verify if there are any words in the string. If the list of words (words) is empty, return 0, indicating that there are no words in the string.
3.Returning Length of Last Word:If there are words in the string, return the length of the last word by accessing the last element in the list of words (words[-1]) and finding its length using the len() function.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(k)
